Fixed	The autoindentation now also can handle wrapped lines with additonal trailing line comments.
Fixed	Curvilinear coordinates do now work more consistent across the plotting types.
Cleaned	The duplicate code detection feature does not use end points of control flow statements as starting points any longer.
Cleaned	The internal memory consumption of single values was reduced.
Cleaned	Improved the return of "fwt", especially the enumeration of the coefficients.
New	A logger object is now available.
New	Dict object can be used to map between two arbitrary types (requiring that the key type to supports a "less-than" relation).
Cleaned	Dict object are now abbreviated with "DCT" and DictStructs with "SCT".
Cleaned	The static code analyzer won't mark methods that have no required arguments as lacking their parentheses if the user's intend is to stick with the default arguments.
Fixed	A rare crash that occured if tabs in the data viewer are dragged around, has been resolved.
Applied	The method TAB().replacevals() does now accept a scalar value as a common replacement value for a vector or values.
Updated	All occurences of regular expressions have been updated to be more runtime-efficient.
Removed	Due to the highly flexible argument list of drawing functions, those are not checked by the code analyzer any more.
Added	The path object now has the two methods "twig" for getting the parent entry of the leaf and "leafless" for returning a new path without the current leaf.
Fixed	The code analyzer now understands better, what a wrapped line is and will examine the whole (logical) line at once.
Fixed	The new code parser will handle more constants and heuristics won't get overwritten by generic types like "any" any longer.
Added	Functions for bit-level logic and manipulation haven been added: "bitand()", "bitor()", "bitxor()", "bitnot()", "bitshift()", "bitmask()" and "bitcast()"
Added	The table method "TAB().convert()" will now also try to convert to a categorical column, if the second argument is set to "auto".
Applied	Tables do now also correctly handle the "duration" data type.
Cleaned	Tables do now favor "value.f64" over the previous behavior of converting to "value.cf64". This will save a lot of space in many cases.
Updated	The package repository is now located in GitHub simplyfing the contribution process.
Applied	It is possible to have secondary package repositories (even private ones), if they provide a similar REST API as GitHub or Gitlab.
Cleaned	The return value of "url" is now always STR, even if the contents are byte counts. This is to make some special cases more robust.
Added	It is now possible to enforce an HTTP method in "url" by prefixing the URL in the command with the desired method.
Cleaned	The encoding of package files is now also UTF-8.
Fixed	Passing a component of an object.path vector as input for another function does not result in a crash anymore.
Fixed	Commands, which are used without any expression or parameter, do not result in a substr error anymore.
Cleaned	The tooltips for plugin commands have been updated to reflect their signature better.
Fixed	Return values of plugins work again as intended.
Applied	The package repository indexes are now more robust against missing network connection or REST API rate-limits.
